A production-ready **Express.js + TypeScript boilerplate** with:

- Prisma ORM (PostgreSQL)
- JWT Authentication (Access + Refresh Tokens)
- Role-based access control
- Socket.io for real-time communication
- Structured logging with Pino
- Zod validation + OpenAPI docs
- Cookie handling
- Clean architecture: Controller â†’ Service â†’ Repository â†’ DTO â†’ Model
- Global error handling & standard API responses


## âš¡ Installation

1. Clone the repo:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/express-boilerplate.git
cd express-boilerplate

Install dependencies: npm install

Install dev dependencies (TypeScript + types): npm install -D typescript ts-node ts-node-dev @types/node @types/cookie-parser

Setup Prisma:
- npx prisma generate
- npx prisma migrate dev --name init

Create .env:

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/mydb?schema=public"
JWT_SECRET="your_jwt_secret"
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET="your_jwt_refresh_secret"
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=5000
ðŸš€ Running the Project:
Development
npm run dev

Uses ts-node-dev for hot-reload

Production
npm run build
npm start

Scripts:
"scripts": {
  "dev": "ts-node-dev --respawn --transpile-only src/server.ts",
  "build": "tsc",
  "start": "node dist/server.js",
  "prisma:generate": "prisma generate",
  "prisma:migrate": "prisma migrate dev",
  "prisma:deploy": "prisma migrate deploy"
}
Authentication Endpoints

Register: POST /api/v1/auth/register

Login: POST /api/v1/auth/login

Refresh Token: POST /api/v1/auth/refresh

Logout: POST /api/v1/auth/logout

Example Request (Register/Login):

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

Example Response:

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Login successful",
  "data": {
    "accessToken": "<jwt_access_token>",
    "refreshToken": "<jwt_refresh_token>"
  }
}